# Successful Login After Brute Force

## Overview
This scenario builds on the brute-force attack. After multiple failed attempts, I logged in using valid credentials to simulate account compromise.

## Attack Execution
Manual login:
- Username: test
- Password: Password123!

## Detection in Wazuh
Relevant logs:
- Event ID 4624 – Successful logon

## Analysis
What makes this interesting is the context:
- login success happened shortly after multiple failures
- same source IP was involved

Individually, a successful login is normal. In sequence, it becomes suspicious.

## MITRE ATT&CK
T1078 – Valid Accounts

## Takeaway
Correlation matters more than individual events. This is where SIEM becomes useful.
